Note: ============================================================================
Note: Expression Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Binary expressions use the operator-in-middle layout dart_to_hir reads:
left operand (0), operator identifier node whose value is the operator
spelling (1), right operand (2). map_binary_operator dispatches on the
spelling string, so the parser stores the exact source lexeme.
@End Reasoning
Process called "make_binary_node" takes left as Integer, op_lexeme as Integer, right as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build a DART_BINARY_EXPR with operator at child 1

    Let binary be proc create_ast_node with DART_BINARY_EXPR
    proc add_node_child with binary, left
    Let op_node be proc create_value_node with DART_IDENTIFIER, op_lexeme
    proc add_node_child with binary, op_node
    proc add_node_child with binary, right
    Return binary
End Process

@Reasoning:
The expression entry point starts the precedence chain at assignment, the
loosest expression operator in Dart.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse expression (entry point)

    Return proc parse_assignment_expression with parser
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns 1 when a token is one of Dart's assignment operators (plain,
compound arithmetic/bitwise/shift, and null-coalescing ??=).
@End Reasoning
Process called "token_is_assignment_operator" takes token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check whether a token is an assignment operator

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PLUS_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MINUS_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STAR_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SLASH_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TILDE_SLASH_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PERCENT_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_AMPERSAND_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PIPE_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CARET_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LEFT_SHIFT_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_RIGHT_SHIFT_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_QUESTION_QUESTION_EQUAL from Lexer:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
"lhs OP= rhs" with right associativity ("a = b = c" assigns c to b first).
Emits DART_ASSIGNMENT_EXPR with lhs (0), operator identifier node (1),
rhs (2) - the layout translate_assignment_expression and
map_assignment_operator consume.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_assignment_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse assignment expression (right-associative)

    Let left be proc parse_conditional_expression with parser

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
    Let is_assign be proc token_is_assignment_operator with token_type
    If is_assign is equal to 1:
        Let op_lexeme be proc current_lexeme with parser
        proc advance_parser with parser

        Let right be proc parse_assignment_expression with parser

        Let assign be proc create_ast_node with DART_ASSIGNMENT_EXPR
        proc add_node_child with assign, left
        Let op_node be proc create_value_node with DART_IDENTIFIER, op_lexeme
        proc add_node_child with assign, op_node
        proc add_node_child with assign, right
        Return assign
    End If

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
"cond ? then : else" - right-associative; condition (0), then (1),
else (2) per translate_ternary_expression. The branches recurse at the
conditional level so nested ternaries group rightward.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_conditional_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse conditional (ternary) expression

    Let expr be proc parse_null_coalescing_expression with parser

    Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_QUESTION from Lexer:
        proc advance_parser with parser

        Let ternary be proc create_ast_node with DART_CONDITIONAL_EXPR
        proc add_node_child with ternary, expr

        Let then_expr be proc parse_conditional_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with ternary, then_expr

        proc expect_token with parser, TOKEN_COLON from Lexer

        Let else_expr be proc parse_conditional_expression with parser
        proc add_node_child with ternary, else_expr

        Return ternary
    End If

    Return expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
"a ?? b" sits between the conditional and logical-or levels in Dart.
Emits the dedicated DART_NULL_AWARE_EXPR node (left 0, right 1) that
translate_null_aware_expression lowers to the HIR null-coalesce opcode.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_null_coalescing_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse null-coalescing expression (??)

    Let left be proc parse_logical_or_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_QUESTION_QUESTION from Lexer:
            proc advance_parser with parser
            Let right be proc parse_logical_or_expression with parser

            Let null_aware be proc create_ast_node with DART_NULL_AWARE_EXPR
            proc add_node_child with null_aware, left
            proc add_node_child with null_aware, right
            Set left to null_aware
        Otherwise:
            Return left
        End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
"||" - left-associative, looser than &&.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_logical_or_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse logical OR expression

    Let left be proc parse_logical_and_expression with parser

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc current_token_type with parser
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_OR_OR from Lexer:
            Let op_lexeme be proc current_lexeme with parser
            proc advance_parser with parser
            Let right be proc parse_logical_and_expression with parser
            Set left to proc make_binary_node with left, op_lexeme, right
        Otherwise:
            Return left
        End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
"&&" - left-associative, between || and equality.
@End Reasoning
Process called "parse_logical_and_expression" takes parser as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse logical AND expression

    Let left be proc parse_equality_expression with parser

